# Auto-Refresh Enhancements Walkthrough

The auto-refresh functionality in the surgery schedule has been upgraded to be configurable and less intrusive.

## Key Changes

### 1. Settings UI Improvements
- The settings menu now contains an **Update Interval** selector.
- The interval options are: 1, 3, 5, and 10 minutes.
- Refined the "Auto-update" checkbox label for clarity.

### 2. Default-Off Behavior
- Auto-refresh is now **OFF by default** for new users or upon clearing local storage.
- It respects the user's previously saved preference if available.

### 3. Dynamic Interval Logic
- The [setupAutoRefresh](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html#5093-5117) function now reads the preferred interval from `localStorage`.
- Changing the interval in the settings menu immediately applies the new rate if auto-refresh is enabled.

### 4. Smart Pause/Resume
- **Pause**: Refresh cycles are automatically skipped if the Patient Detail view or Anesthesia Evaluation form is open.
- **Resume**: The refresh timer is reset and restarted whenever a detail view or evaluation form is closed, ensuring the background process stays aligned with user activity.

## Verification Results

### UI and Persistence
- [x] Settings menu correctly displays "Auto-update" and "Update Interval".
- [x] Initial state is correctly derived (Defaults to OFF, 5 minutes).
- [x] Settings are persisted in `localStorage` across page reloads.

### Logic Verification
- [x] [setupAutoRefresh](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html#5093-5117) correctly clears existing timers before starting new ones.
- [x] [closeDetail](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html#3832-3840) and [closeEvalModal](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html#4305-4313) trigger [setupAutoRefresh](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html#5093-5117) to restart the timer.
- [x] `setInterval` uses the dynamically retrieved interval from `localStorage`.

